				\begin{document}$$P = \left[ {Ivv-Ivh} \right]/\left[ {Ivv + Ivh} \right]$$\end{document}P=Ivv-Ivh∕Ivv+Ivhwhere Ivv is the emission intensity measured when the excitation and emission polarizers are parallel, and Ivh is the emission intensity measured when the emission and excitation polarizers are oriented perpendicular to each other. The degree of polarization is expressed by the unit mP, or a 0.001 ratio between (Ivv − Ivh) and (Ivv + Ivh)28.
